data.title: Not Sure How to Rate this, It was our first time, so don't have anything to compare it with
data.text: For me, It was "okay". Not really good, and not really bad. So being our first time this review might not mean anything.  I had the orange chicken, and it was okay.  Tasted like the orange chicken we get from the deli at Safeway.

data.title: Top Shelf, Spicy Chinese Food-Gourmet Style
data.text:
This is our favorite Chinese food restaurant in the Willamette Valley. Gourmet level. Can be spicy. Very high quality food-very fresh. 
The restaurant is small and cozy. The food is so good you have to ask for soy sauce (which the food really doesn't need).
The owners really take an artisan's pride in their creations.
My fav is the Kung Pao. Spicy w/ white meat Chicken.
